Irb is a pain to work with&hellip; when you don&rsquo;t know it enough. Fortunately, it can be configured extensively enough to make your Ruby interactive sessions much smoother. Pocahontas asked me to post my Irb configuration: # ~/.irbrc IRB.conf[:AUTO_INDENT] = true IRB.conf[:USE_READLINE] = true IRB.conf[:SAVE_HISTORY] = 5000 IRB.conf[:HISTORY_FILE] = &ldquo;#{ENV[&lsquo;HOME&rsquo;]}/.irb_history&rdquo; IRB.conf[:PROMPT_MODE] = :SIMPLE
require &lsquo;irb/completion&rsquo; require &lsquo;irb/ext/save-history&rsquo; require &lsquo;pp&rsquo;
